jmraidctl - JMB39x/JMS56x RAID Controller Tool

Command-line tool for managing JMicron JMB39x and JMS56x SATA
hardware RAID controllers without the X-based HWRaidManager.

Commands
--------
  (none)            Show RAID and disk status (default)
  alarm-mute 0|1    Unmute/mute the RAID alarm
  identify P 0|1    Turn disk P LED off/on for identification
  standby M         Set disk standby timer (0-255 minutes, 0=disabled)
  rebuild-priority  Set rebuild priority (highest/high/medium/low/lowest)
  rebuild-status    Show rebuild progress

Usage
-----
  ./jmraidctl /dev/sgX                  Show RAID status
  ./jmraidctl /dev/sgX alarm-mute 1     Mute alarm
  ./jmraidctl /dev/sgX identify 0 1     Blink disk 0 LED
  ./jmraidctl /dev/sgX standby 30       30-minute standby timer
  ./jmraidctl /dev/sgX rebuild-priority medium
  ./jmraidctl /dev/sgX rebuild-status
  ./jmraidctl -h                        Show help

Building
--------
  make

